FBIS3-9481 "dreeu058_i_94011" FBIS-EEU-94-058 Document Type:Daily Report 24 Mar 1994 BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA Attacks on Brcko Defense Lines Continue AU2403153194 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in Serbo-Croatian 1400 GMT 24 Mar 94 AU2403153194 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network Language: Serbo-Croatian Article Type:BFN [Report by Hamid Deronjic and Nihad Culihovic] [Excerpt] The shelling of the central section of the Brcko defense, which has been pounded with tanks and 120-mm mortars since 0630, has in the meantime been stepped up with fire from 122-mm howitzers, mortars of [word indistinct] and 82-mm, [word indistinct] and recoilless guns. Chetnik antiaircraft guns, brownings, portable mortars, and snipers are attacking almost all parts of our defense. There have been no infantry attacks yet, which clearly indicates what the real aim of the Serbian aggressor is, namely to destroy as much as it can and to kill as many people as possible on the free territory. [passage omitted]
